cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically object detection and scene classification in remote sensing images. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel architecture for multi-orientation object detection, which involves training a neural network to be sensitive to object rotations. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of a loss function to evaluate the rotation-invariance of the network, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on natural images, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
